$ System.Management.Automation.CmdletBindingAttribute (class)

A → Windows/PowerShell/language/function[PowerShell function] tht is defined with the `cmdletBinding` attribute uses → Windows/PowerShell/language/cmdlet[PowerShell cmdLet] rather than script parameter binding.

`System.Management.Automation.CmdletBindingAttribute` derives indirectly from → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Attribute[`System.Attribute`].

The → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Management/Automation/FunctionInfo#dn-FunctionInfo-CmdletBinding[`CmdletBinding` property of the `FunctionInfo` class] reveals if the corresponding function was
defined with the `CmdletBinding` attribute.

sa:
  The influence of the `cmdletBinding` attribute on the → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/PsCmdLet[PowerShell automatic variable `$psCmdLet`].
